%U A037267 110023430413866989085481236650825620965529772963665402006849147440648610889146
%N A037267 Number of Boolean functions on n inputs with representing polynomial of max degree n.
%C A037267 For n >= 1, a(n) is the number of n-variable non-balanced Boolean functions. A Boolean function is non-balanced if it takes the values 0 and 1 not an equal number of times. - _Thomas Scheuerle_, Apr 17 2026
%H A037267 Aniruddha Biswas and Palash Sarkar, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.14069">Counting unate and balanced monotone Boolean functions</a>, arXiv:2304.14069 [math.CO], 2023.
%H A037267 Aniruddha Biswas and Palash Sarkar, <a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/journals/JIS/VOL28/Biswas/biswas6.html">Counting Unate and Monotone Boolean Functions Under Restrictions of Balancedness and Non-Degeneracy</a>, J. Int. Seq. (2025) Vol. 28, Art. No. 25.3.4. See p. 2.
%H A037267 <a href="/index/Bo#Boolean">Index entries for sequences related to Boolean functions</a>
%F A037267 a(n) = A001146(n) - A037293(n).
%F A037267 From _Thomas Scheuerle_, Apr 17 2026: (Start)
%F A037267 a(n) = A045621(2^n).
%F A037267 a(n) = 2^(2^n) - binomial(2^n, 2^(n-1)), for n > 0. (End)
%o A037267 (PARI) a(n) = 2^(2^n) - (2^n)!/(2^(n-1))!^2 \\ _Thomas Scheuerle_, Apr 17 2026
%Y A037267 Cf. A001146, A037293, A045621.
